## 1. Design Philosophy

| Principle | What it means in practice |
|-----------|--------------------------|
| **Calm productivity** | No loud gradients or heavy chrome. Plenty of whitespace. The task content is the hero. |
| **Speed first** | Every action feels instant via optimistic updates. Skeleton loaders replace blank screens. |
| **Glanceable** | Priority, due date, and status must be readable in under one second per row. |
| **Progressive disclosure** | Show the minimum fields first; reveal extras on demand (quick-add → full detail). |
| **Keyboard-native** | Every core action reachable without a mouse. |
| **Accessible by default** | WCAG 2.1 AA contrast ratios, focus rings, ARIA labels baked in from day one — not bolted on at the end. |

