### 7.3 Inbox / Project View

#### Task List

```
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Work                                 ⊞ Filter  ↕ Sort │
│  12 tasks · 3 completed today                          │
│  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━  │
│  ⠿  ○  Design new landing page         🔴 Today   ●●  │
│  ⠿  ○  Write API docs                  🟠 Fri    ●    │
│  ⠿  ●  Set up CI pipeline              ✓ Done         │
│  ⠿  ○  Review pull requests            — No date  ●   │
│                                                        │
│  + Add a task…                                         │
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Task row anatomy (left → right):**
1. Drag handle (`⠿`) — visible on hover only
2. Checkbox circle — click to complete; animates checkmark + row fades with strikethrough
3. Task title — `text-base`; completed tasks get `text-secondary line-through`
4. Spacer (flex-grow)
5. Label chips (up to 2 visible; `+N more` if more)
6. Due date badge — shows `Today` in amber, `Overdue` in red, otherwise `Mon 14`
7. Priority dot — coloured circle using priority color tokens
8. Assignee avatar — 20px circle, shown only in team projects

**Hover state on row:**
- Row background → `bg-neutral-50`
- Drag handle becomes visible
- Show context menu button (···) at far right

**Quick-Add bar:**
- Shown at the bottom of the list (or top in "Today" view)
- Placeholder: "Add a task…"
- On click: expands to show title input + due date + priority picker inline
- Press `Enter` to save, `Esc` to cancel

**Bulk selection:**
- Clicking a checkbox while holding `Shift` selects a range
- Checkbox column appears on left when any task is selected
- `BulkActionBar` slides up from the bottom: "3 selected · Complete · Move · Label · Delete"

