## 9. Responsive Behaviour

### Breakpoints

| Name | Width | Layout |
|------|-------|--------|
| Mobile | < 640px | Single column; no sidebar; bottom tab nav |
| Tablet | 640px–1023px | Collapsible sidebar; task detail as full-screen modal |
| Desktop | ≥ 1024px | Full 3-column split view |
| Wide | ≥ 1280px | Detail panel increases to 420px |

### Mobile-Specific Patterns

- **Bottom Tab Bar** (`MobileNav.tsx`): Today · Inbox · Search · Profile — fixed at bottom, 64px tall, safe area inset respected
- **Sidebar as Drawer**: swipe right or tap hamburger to reveal; closes on backdrop tap or swipe left
- **Task Detail**: opens as full-screen page (not a panel); back button top-left returns to list
- **Quick-Add**: floating `+` button bottom-right (FAB) at 56px; tap to open bottom sheet with task form
- **Drag-and-Drop**: disabled on touch (use long-press context menu to move instead)
- **Swipe actions on task rows**: swipe left to reveal "Delete" (red) and "Archive" (gray) actions

### Tablet-Specific Patterns

- Sidebar is 200px and collapsible
- Task detail opens as a modal dialog (not side panel)
- Command palette available via keyboard

