## 10. Dark Mode

Implemented via `class="dark"` on `<html>` (Tailwind's `darkMode: 'class'` strategy). The `uiStore` persists the preference to `localStorage`. System preference read via `matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)')`.

### Dark Mode Tokens

```css
.dark {
  --bg-app:         #0f1117;
  --bg-surface:     #1a1d27;
  --bg-subtle:      #22263a;
  --bg-overlay:     rgba(0,0,0,0.6);

  --text-primary:   #f3f4f6;
  --text-secondary: #9ca3af;
  --text-disabled:  #4b5563;

  --border-default: #2d3148;
  --border-strong:  #3d4266;
}
```

**Dark mode rules:**
- Never use `bg-white` directly — always use `--bg-surface` token
- Shadows should be reduced (they disappear in dark; use `border` for elevation instead)
- Chart colours stay the same hue but increase lightness by 10% for contrast
- Priority colours stay the same (they're already saturated enough)
- Images and avatars: no change needed

