## 11. Accessibility

Target: **WCAG 2.1 AA** compliance.

### Colour Contrast
- All text on backgrounds must meet 4.5:1 (normal text) or 3:1 (large text / UI components)
- Test with the [Colour Contrast Analyser](https://www.tpgi.com/color-contrast-checker/) before shipping each component
- `--text-secondary` on `--bg-surface` must be checked in both light and dark modes

### Focus Management
- All interactive elements must have a visible focus ring: `outline: 2px solid var(--border-focus); outline-offset: 2px`
- Never use `outline: none` without a custom replacement
- Modal open: focus moves to modal; Esc closes modal and returns focus to trigger button
- Task detail panel open: focus moves to title

### ARIA Roles and Labels
- Task checkbox: `role="checkbox"` + `aria-checked` + `aria-label="Complete [task title]"`
- Drag handle: `aria-roledescription="sortable"` + instruction in `aria-describedby`
- Priority badge: `aria-label="Priority: Urgent"`
- Notification bell: `aria-label="Notifications (3 unread)"` (updates dynamically)
- Loading skeletons: `aria-busy="true"` on their container
- Toast messages: `role="status"` or `role="alert"` depending on urgency

### Keyboard Navigation
- Tab order follows reading order (sidebar → header → task list → detail panel)
- Task rows are keyboard-focusable; `Enter` opens detail; `Space` toggles complete
- Dropdown menus: `↑↓` to navigate, `Enter` to select, `Esc` to close
- Drag-and-drop has a keyboard alternative: focus a task → `Space` to "pick up" → `↑↓` to move → `Space` to drop

### Screen Reader Considerations
- Live regions (`aria-live="polite"`) for: real-time updates, toast messages, task complete confirmations
- `aria-live="assertive"` only for errors
- Avoid icon-only buttons without `aria-label`

