## 13. Loading & Skeleton States

Skeletons are preferred over spinners for page-level loads. Spinners are used for button actions.

### Skeleton Patterns

**Task list loading:**
```
⟨skeleton: checkbox 16px⟩  ⟨skeleton: title 60% width⟩  ⟨skeleton: badge 48px⟩
⟨skeleton: checkbox 16px⟩  ⟨skeleton: title 45% width⟩  ⟨skeleton: badge 48px⟩
⟨skeleton: checkbox 16px⟩  ⟨skeleton: title 72% width⟩  ⟨skeleton: badge 48px⟩
```

**Detail panel loading:**
- Title: full-width skeleton at `text-xl` height
- Properties block: 6 rows of label + value skeletons
- Comment section: 2 avatar + text block skeletons

**Sidebar loading:**
- 5 rows of skeleton nav items
- 3 skeleton project items

### Spinner Usage
- Used inside buttons when action is in-flight: `<Loader2 className="animate-spin" size={16} />`
- Button becomes `disabled` + cursor `not-allowed` during load
- Never show a page-level spinner; always use skeletons instead

### Optimistic Updates
Tasks are updated immediately in the UI before the API responds. On API error:
1. Revert the change
2. Show error toast: "Failed to update task. [Retry]"

